modules.description: Handles asynchronous logging by providing functions to create, configure, and send log entries. Operates on log records containing timestamps, severity levels, and message payloads. Used to integrate real-time error tracking and monitoring into event-driven applications.

Provides functions to create log reporters with different output formats, including plain, JSON, and compressed Zstandard streams, and supports custom output handlers. Works with logging levels, source identifiers, and asynchronous writer interfaces. Used to configure logging behavior dynamically via command-line arguments, including setting log levels and color output for specific sources.
